TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {18388=Personal: Full name is  Kerri Shaquil Washington Belcher...Born on June 28, 1993 in Roanoke, Va…Daughter of Arthur Belcher and Barbara Washington…Has one brother, James Washington, and two sisters, Shameka Washington and Breanna Belcher…Majoring in pre-professional biology with a minor in pyschology…Plans to attend medical school., 18043=High School: Graduated from Oak Hill Academy in Mouth of Wilson, Va…Coached by Mike Rogers…Kerri was Unsung Hero in 2007-2008, MVP 2008-2009, second district team 2008-2009, Honorable Mention 2007-2009 and first district team 2009-2010…Kerri averaged nine points and eight rebounds per game in high school., 17397=As a freshman (2011-2012): Played in 25 games, including 18 starts…Averaged 6.8 points and five rebounds per game…Scored in double figures in seven games…Posted a double-double with 17 points and a season-high 10 rebounds at Hiwassee (Nov. 28)…Nearly recorded a double-double with 10 points and nine rebounds against Pfeiffer (Jan. 7)…Tallied 10 points and nine boards against Converse (Jan. 24)…Season-high 18 points on 6-of-11 shooting at Barton (Jan. 28)…Equaled her season-high of 18 points with a 7-for-12 night against St. Andrews (Feb. 11)…Posted 16 points on 7-of-14 shooting against King (Feb. 14).}
